HEADWORD: Crossrow
<hw>Cross"row`</hw> <pr>(-r?`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
alphabet; -- called also <altname>Christcross-row</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And from the <qex>crossrow</qex> plucks the letter G.</q>
<rj><qau> Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A row that crosses others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossruff</ent>⟦br⟧
